    {% block usages %}
        <section class="informative">
            <h2>General usage guidelines</h2>

            The DCAT-AP-LU profile was developed in the context of the national DGA implementation but is intended to be
            usable in other contexts. The usage guidance is subdivided accordingly.

            <h3>Usage guide on Datasets and Distributions </h3>

            The
            <a href="https://semiceu.github.io/DCAT-AP/releases/3.0.0/#usage-guide-on-datasets-distributions-and-data-services">general
                usage guide</a> for [[DCAT-AP-v3.0]] applies for most of DCAT-AP-LU. The main differences for this
            profile
            include:

            <ul>
                <li><a href="#Dataset.identifier">Dataset.identifier</a>: This property is mandatory to promote
                    interoperability and data governance best practice. For the Luxembourg public sector, an identifier
                    strategy is under development.
                </li>
                <li><a href="#Dataset.dataprotectiontype">Dataset.dataProtectionType</a>: This new property is
                    applicable in
                    the DGA context only (see below).
                </li>
                <li><a href="#Dataset.inseries">Dataset.inSeries</a>: This property was upgraded from optional to
                    recommended. More guidance to follow.
                </li>
                <li><a href="#Dataset.accessrights">Dataset.rights</a>: The accepted values for this property are
                    restricted to "public" and "non-public".
                </li>
                <li><a href="#Dataset.type">Dataset.type</a>: The accepted values for this property have been adapted as
                    described in [[[#controlled-vocs]]].
                </li>
                <li><a href="#Distribution.mediatype">Distribution.mediaType</a>: This property was upgraded from
                    optional
                    to recommended due to the greater granularity of the associated vocabulary compared to <a
                            href="#Distribution.mediatype">Distribution.mediaType</a>.
                </li>
                <li><a href="#Distribution.haspolicy">Distribution.hasPolicy</a>: DCAT-AP-LU provides extended usage
                    guidance for expressing data use restrictions using [[ODRL]] and [[DUO]].
                </li>
            </ul>

            Except for the properties in the list above, the property type (mandatory, recommended or optional) was
            adopted
            as-is from [[DCAT-AP-v3.0]]. The overall format of this specification only expressly highlights
            whether a property is mandatory or not, via the `Card` column in the
            <a href="#main-entities">Main Entities tables</a>. The further distinction between recommended and optional
            properties, while widely used in DCAT-AP, is not considered. Please refer to the <a href="
        " https://semiceu.github.io/DCAT-AP/releases/3.0.0/#quick-reference>Quick reference table in Appendix A</a> in
            [[DCAT-AP-v3.0]] for an overview of recommended and optional properties.


            <h3>Usage guide for the DGA context</h3>

            <h4 id="dataprotection_guidance">
                <a href="#Dataset.dataprotectiontype">Dataset.dataProtectionType</a>
            </h4>

            Any metadata record for a protected dataset published in the context of the DGA must include at least one of
            Any metadata record for a protected dataset published in the context of the DGA must include at least one of
            the
            6 controlled vocabulary terms listed in [[[#controlled-vocs]]] (:PersonalData,
            :CommerciallyConfidentialData,
            :IntellectualPropertyData, :StatisticallyConfidentialData, :SpecialCategoryPersonalData,
            :ProfessionalConfidentialData). These properties originate from, and are maintained by, the Data
Privacy Vocabulary [[DPV]].

            <h4 id="legislation_guidance"><a href="#Dataset.applicablelegislation">Dataset.applicableLegislation</a>
            </h4>

            Any metadata record for a dataset published in the context of the DGA must include a reference to the
            relevant
            law articles (links TBA) to define whether the dataset may be reused under the definition of "TITRE V –
            Traitement ultérieur de données à caractère personnel par les entités publiques" (TUDP), "TITRE VI –Accès
            et réutilisation des données détenues par des organismes du secteur public par des réutilisateurs dedonnées"
            (ARD) or both. A metadata record that does not include at least one of these references will notbe
            considered valid. Exact [[ELI]] compliant URIs for the different contexts will be included here once the
            lawtext
            has been officially adopted and published.


            <h4 id="sample_guidance"><a href="#Dataset.sample">Dataset.sample</a></h4>

            In order to facilitate the creation and assessment of data access requests for datasets in the DGA context,
            the
            associated metadata record should include data dictionaries whenever possible. Data dictionaries should be
            included via a special type of distribution referenced from the <a href="#Dataset.sample">Dataset.sample</a>
            property. This guidance reuses the implementation model proposed by the
            <a href="https://healthdcat-ap.github.io/#sample-distribution">HealthDCAT-AP</a> metadata profile.
            <br>
            No specific format is imposed for the data dictionary. Machine-readable tabular formats such as CSV or TSV
            are
            preferred. A minimal set of properties to be included in a data dictionary is under development and will be
            made
            available in due course.

            <h4 id="policy_guidance"><a href="#Distribution.haspolicy">Distribution.hasPolicy</a></h4>

            DCAT-AP-LU leverages existing mechanisms from [[ODRL]] and [[DUO]] to enable data holders to specify
            additional
            restrictions on data reuse in a consistent and machine-readable fashion.

            The following points are expressed:

            <ul>
                <li>Restrictions can be expressed as either permissions or prohibitions.</li>
                <li>The default odrl:policy type is odrl:Set but policies of type odrl:Offer may also be used.</li>
                <li>The default odrl:action for all scenarios is odrl:use</li>
                <li>Permitted constraint types (odrl:leftOperand) for constraints are odrl:Purpose/dpv:Purpose,
                    dateTime,
                    spatial and industry.
                </li>
                <li>Permitted constraint modifiers (odrl:rightOperand) are:
                    <ul>
                        <li>Temporal restrictions: an [[ISO8601]] compliant Date and Time value.</li>
                        <li>Spatial restrictions: a valid geospatial area expression such as an [[ISO3166]]
                            Country Code.
                        </li>
                        <li>Purpose restrictions: one of the data use restrictions specified in the table below.</li>
                        <li>Industry restrictions: <i>list under development</i></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>

            <table class="data-table simple">
                <thead>
                <tr class="data-table__header">
                    <th class="data-table__header-title" style="width:15%">
                        Property
                    </th>
                    <th class="data-table__header-title" style="width:25%">
                        Label (shorthand)
                    </th>
                    <th class="data-table__header-title" style="width:30%">
                        Definition
                    </th>
                    <th class="data-table__header-title" style="width:30%">
                        Comment
                    </th>
                </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000018</td>
                    <td>not for profit, non commercial use only (NPUNCU)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations
                        and
                        not-for-profit use, non-commercial use.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000046</td>
                    <td>non-commercial use only (NCU)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use of the data is limited to not-for-profit use.</td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000045</td>
                    <td>not for profit organisation use only (NPU)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use of the data is limited to not-for-profit
                        organizations.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000015</td>
                    <td>no general methods research (NMDS)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use does not allow methods development research (e.g.,
                        development of software or algorithms).
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000019</td>
                    <td>publication required (PUB)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that the requestor agrees to make results of studies using the
                        data
                        available to the larger scientific community.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000024</td>
                    <td>publication moratorium (MOR)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that the requestor agrees not to publish results of studies
                        until a
                        specific date.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000021</td>
                    <td>ethics approval required (IRB)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that the requestor must provide documentation of local IRB/ERB
                        approval.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000020</td>
                    <td>collaboration required (COL)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that the requestor must agree to collaboration with the primary
                        study investigator(s).
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000012</td>
                    <td>research specific restrictions (RS)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use is limited to studies of a certain research type.</td>
                    <td>Requires specification of permitted research types, e.g. structured as a sub-term of <a
                            href="http://edamontology.org/topic_0003">Topic (EDAM:0003)</a> or free text
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000029</td>
                    <td>return to database or resource (RTN)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that the requestor must return derived/enriched data to the
                        database/resource.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000042</td>
                    <td>general research use (GRU)</td>
                    <td>This data use permission indicates that use is allowed for general research use for any research
                        purpose.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000043</td>
                    <td>clinical care use (CC)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use is allowed for clinical use and care.</td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000007</td>
                    <td>disease specific research (DS)</td>
                    <td>This data use permission indicates that use is allowed provided it is related to the specified
                        disease.
                    </td>
                    <td>Requires specification of permitted diseases, e.g. structured as a sub-term of <a
                            href="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MONDO_0000001">disease (MONDO:0000001)</a> or free text
                    </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000016</td>
                    <td>genetic studies only (GSO)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates that use is limited to genetic studies only (i.e., studies that
                        include genotype research alone or both genotype and phenotype research, but not phenotype
                        research
                        exclusively)
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000006</td>
                    <td>health or medical or biomedical research (HMB)</td>
                    <td>This data use permission indicates that use is allowed for health/medical/biomedical purposes;
                        does
                        not include the study of population origins or ancestry.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000011</td>
                    <td>population origins or ancestry research only (POA)</td>
                    <td>This data use permission indicates that use of the data is limited to the study of population
                        origins or ancestry.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>DUO:0000044</td>
                    <td>population origins or ancestry research prohibited (NPOA)</td>
                    <td>This data use modifier indicates use for purposes of population, origin, or ancestry research is
                        prohibited.
                    </td>
                    <td>&nbsp;</td>
                </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
